Practical No. 6: GitHub Collaboration using Pull Request

Aim
To collaborate using Fork, Pull Request and review mechanism in GitHub.

Procedure
1. Open GitHub in your browser and login to your GitHub account. Then open any repository that you want to contribute to.

2. Click on the 'Fork' button to create a copy of that repository in your GitHub account.

3. Open Git Bash and clone the forked repository using the command: git clone https://github.com/yourusername/repository-name.git

4. Move into the repository folder using the command: cd repository-name

5. Create a new branch using the command: git branch feature-branch

6. Switch to the new branch using the command: git checkout feature-branch

7. Open any file (for example file1.txt) and add some changes such as: 'This change is added for collaboration practical'. Save the file.

8. Add the modified files to staging area using the command: git add .

9. Commit the changes using the command: git commit -m 'Added changes for pull request'

10. Push the branch to GitHub using the command: git push origin feature-branch

11. Go to your repository on GitHub and click on 'Compare & Pull Request'.

12. Add a title and description for the pull request and click 'Create Pull Request'.

13. Review the pull request and click 'Merge Pull Request'.

14. Click 'Confirm Merge' to complete the merge process.

15. Finally, check the commits section of the repository to verify that the changes are merged successfully.

Result
The repository was forked, cloned locally, changes were made in a branch and a pull request was created and merged successfully.
